description.plain:
All Time Low is an American pop-punk band hailing from Baltimore. The band currently consists of lead vocalist and rhythm guitarist Alex Gaskarth, lead guitarist and backing vocalist Jack Barakat, bassist and backing vocalist Zack Merrick and drummer Rian Dawson.

The band formed in 2003, while the band members were still in high school, and started off covering Blink-182 tracks. After the band went through some lineup changes to the current lineup that exists today, they released their debut EP The Three Words to Remember in Dealing with the End in 2004. The band debated calling themselves Playground-X after a level from the popular shooter game Counter-Strike but eventually settled on All Time Low from New Found Glory’s “Head On Collision”.

Their first full length The Party Scene was released 2005, which was followed by the band members graduating high school in 2006. After graduating, the band was offered a record deal with American label Hopeless Records, who they released their sophomore EP Put Up Or Shut Up with. This EP reached chart success, which lead to the emergence of the band through the mainstream.

The band’s pop-punk style continued to break them into commercial success with their second album So Wrong, It’s Right, which spawned their platinum-certified single “Dear Maria, Count Me In”  in 2006 and their third album Nothing Personal in 2009. 2009 also saw the band announcing their signing to major label Interscope Records, however their first live album Straight to DVD, released in 2010, was still released through Hopeless.

2011’s Dirty Work saw the band head in a more pop-rock direction, but generally it was poorly received by fans of the band. This was then followed by the 2012 album Don’t Panic!, which saw them go back to their pop-punk roots. After the album release, All Time Low left Interscope and went back to Hopeless Records, where they re-released Don’t Panic! as a deluxe edition titled Don’t Panic: It’s Longer Now! in 2013. The re-release contained four new tracks and four acoustic renditions of songs on the original release.

Their 2015 album Future Hearts lead to the release of their second live album Straight to DVD II: Past, Present, and Future Hearts.

In early 2017, All Time Low announced that they were switching their label again to Fueled By Ramen, who released their sixth album Last Young Renegade.

Before completely coming back with another album, All Time Low released a two song EP in 2018: Everything is Fine on Your Birthday.

In April 2020, they released Wake Up, Sunshine, their sophomore album with Fueled By Ramen. This record was vastly different from their last album’s darker sound and was more similar to their classic pop-punk roots. The single “Monsters” featuring blackbear became the biggest song of their career; it spent 18 weeks at #1 on Billboard’s Alternative Airplay chart and entered the Billboard Hot 100 and peaked at #55, becoming the highest-charting song on the Hot 100 for the band.

songs.full_title: Monsters by All Time Low (Ft. ​blackbear)
songs.title: Monsters

description.plain:
“Monsters” is a song about a toxic person who you just can’t let go of. Instead of blaming the person in question, Alex sings lines of self-doubt. It’s a relationship where one person simply can’t let go, like they “don’t mind if you fuck up my life”.

The song features hip-hop artist blackbear and was supposed to have a music video to go with it. Unfortunately the shoot was cancelled due to COVID-19. As a replacement, the band released a lyric video made by Toon53 Productions when the album dropped.

The song is also guitarist Jack Barakat’s favourite from the album, as stated on their Happy Hour livestream.

songs.full_title: Dear Maria, Count Me In by All Time Low
songs.title: Dear Maria, Count Me In

description.plain:
The second single from All Time Low’s second album So Wrong, It’s Right.

Apparently, when the boys got home from tour one time, they ran into an old friend from high school. Turns out she’d become a “entertainer” of sorts- a stripper. Alex was inspired, and voila! Dear Maria was born.

This is the fifth song the band created a music video for.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GcNiKCmWdYE

In late 2020/early 2021, the song made a comeback on the video-sharing platform TikTok, with it becoming an important part of a TikTok trend started by user yungricepatty that band members Alex Gaskarth and Jack Barakat also joined.

songs.full_title: Remembering Sunday by All Time Low (Ft. Juliet Simms)
songs.title: Remembering Sunday

description.plain:
“Remembering Sunday” is the first ballad from All Time Low that fans really connected with. It tells the story of a relationship as fragile as a dream, however it’s obvious that Alex still holds out hope until the end of the song.

Some fans believe that the ending of the song is allusion to suicide, but lead singer Alex Gaskarth disproved that rumour in an interview.

When playing the song live, the band have invited Juliet Simms onstage but have also performed with Cassadee Pope

This song is the band’s fourth most streamed song on Spotify with over 40 million total streams.
